OL,3,CDisability: Lack of assistance by TfW
OL,4,C'makes me question my place in society'
OL,6,F"No one has ever come on the train to
OL,7,Fhelp me get off and onto the platform.
OL,8,FI think that emphasises that the
OL,9,Frights of disabled people to travel
OL,10,Fare not considered.
OL,12,F"When I book that assistance, I ask
OL,13,Ffor help while getting off the train,
OL,14,Fand then to get out of the station.
OL,15,FBut that didn't happen."
OL,17,FTalking about that specific trip, Elin
OL,18,Fsaid that the experience was "not
OL,19,Fperfect, but there were positive
OL,20,Faspects... but there is still room for
OL,21,Fimprovement."
